20/09/2004
TIRANA, Albania -- The interior ministry and intelligence services are looking for two people suspected of involvement in terrorist activities, local media reported Saturday (18 September).
According to some sources, the suspects are Albanians educated in Arab countries, while others say their nationality has not been confirmed.
The information, including photos, reportedly came from foreign security services.
The Albanian forces are conducting searches throughout the country and at major intersections.
(Republika - 19/09/04;
Korrieri - 18/09/04)
